Kakamega Governor Wycliffe Oparanya. [Mumo Munive, Standard]  Governor Wycliffe Oparanya's administration has set aside Sh60 million to support people living with disabilities in the county.  At least 49,000 beneficiaries have been identified in 12 sub-counties, according to the Governor.  Oparanya said the county had conducted a census to establish the number of people living with disabilities, the state in which they live, and their immediate needs.  Kakamega County Headquarters. [Mumo Munive, Standard]  Anger over sewer charges in Kakamega  Wanjigi wants ODM to re-open applications for top party ticket  Gang targeting schools, hotels and bars killed 13 in last one year  Explorer finds huge deposits of high grade gold in Kakamega mines "The census and the need assessment report is what is guiding the county as we implement programmes aimed at uplifting the lives of the disabled persons in the county," he said.  Oparanya said wheelchairs and crutches will be given to disabled persons, and the county will also support their education.  He made the remarks yesterday in his office during a meeting with national officials of the National Council For Persons With Disabilities (NCPWD) led by Executive Director Harun Hassan.  The report showed that many people living with disabilities in the county were living in abject poverty.   Siasa za ODM: Gavana wa Kaunti ya Kakamega, Wycliffe Oparanya anataka aungwe mkono  Kakamega governor Wycliffe Oparanya blames Ford Kenya for the chaos witnessed in kakamega  Chaos erupt In Wetangula’s Bid Launch  By Alexander Chagema | 2 days ago By Alexander Chagema | 3 days ago By John Shilitsa | 4 days ago By Robert Amalemba | 8 days ago